As they talk, Donanâ€™s attention is distracted by a fleshy sound coming from the shadows to one side. 
He moves toward it, deeper into shadows, as the others stay around the Eye. 
We follow Donan as he reaches the nearest pillar. He uses Horadric magic to create a small glow of light, so he can see better. 
The light allows us to see the pillar is moving, the flesh figures in it roiling. Donan takes a step back.
But the flesh pillar reaches out and grabs Donan, pulling him close and stabbing him in the belly. 
The location of the wound must match that shown in Death of Donan scene later (BDD).

Donan collapses to one knee, clutching his wound, as the attention of the others is now drawn to him. 
Before they can come to his side, however, we hear the sound of the other pillars coming to life. The grotesque sound grows in intensity. 
We pull back to reveal multiple pillars coming to life, our group gazing around the chamber, realizing theyâ€™re in deep trouble. 
Donan staggers to his feet, a hand clamped a hand to the wound, as he warns his companions to prepare themselves.
The pillars attack the party.
